The paper deals with measuring and analyzing information diffusion networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing the characteristics of information diffusion networks. "cs.SD" (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a novel measurement framework. "cs.SOC" (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with social networks and their diffusion processes. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a link-tracing based sampling design. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes three different estimators for correcting the bias of sampled data.
